    public void Dispose()
}
```

**Key Details:**
- Uses `ConcurrentQueue<Notification>` for thread-safe notification queuing
- Max queue size: 500 items (enforced with best-effort dequeue)
- `SendNotification()` - two overloads: with/without entityDisplayName
- `GenerateMessage()` - returns user-friendly messages based on EntityOperation
- Message format examples:
  - CREATE: `"New {EntityType} '{DisplayName}' has been created"`
  - UPDATE: `"{EntityType} '{DisplayName}' has been updated"`
  - DELETE: `"{EntityType} '{DisplayName}' has been deleted"`
- If no display name: `"{EntityType} (ID: {entityId})"`
- Default CreatedBy: "System" if userName is null
- `ReceiveNotification()` - dequeues single notification or returns null
- `MarkAsRead()` - currently no-op (persistence not implemented)

